Bloodblade followed silently. He tried hastily to check if any 
memories could come up, but none did.

They entered the lab and Tyrael greeted them.

Tyrael: So, Bloodblade, are you ready for your memory test?

Bloodblade nodded silently. When Tyrael offered a seat, he sat 
silently and waited.

Tyrael took a small electrode-like device and placed it on 
Bloodblade&#39;s temple.

Tyrael: This will boot up a search engine and try to find anything 
in your processor. It&#39;s quite powerful and should be able to find a 
lot in no time. Darkangel, start the program, please.

